s%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20bruising%20in%20her%20face%20and%20swelling%20in%20her%20eyes.%20I%20didn't%20really%20recognise%20her.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20affidavit%20also%20stated%20that%20Scantlebury%20made%20racist%20remarks%20after%20the%20attack%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BIndians%20are%20bad%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20beat%20the%20(expletive)%20out%20of%20an%20Indian%20doctor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20pre-trial%20detention%20hearing%2C%20Palm%20Beach%20County%20Deputy%20Sgt.%20Beth%20Newcomb%20testified%20about%20Scantlebury's%20remarks%2C%20and%20Lal's%20daughter%20described%20the%20severity%20of%20her%20mother's%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScantlebury's%20wife%20testified%20that%20he%20had%20been%20experiencing%20paranoia%20in%20the%20days%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20attack%2C%20believing%20their%20home%20was%20bugged%20and%20that%20he%20was%20under%20surveillance.%20However%2C%20the%20judge%20denied%20a%20request%20to%20transfer%20Scantlebury%20to%20a%20mental%20health%20facility%2C%20calling%20it%20%26quot%3Bpremature.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20has%20sparked%20concerns%20over%20the%20safety%20of%20medical%20professionals%2C%20with%20a%20petition%20calling%20for%20stricter%20security%20measures%20and%20tougher%20penalties%20for%20assaults%20on%20healthcare%20workers%20garnering%20over%2010%2C000%20signatures%20in%20three%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr.%20Cheryl%20Thomas-Harcum%2C%20one%20of%20the%20petition's%20organisers%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BLeela%20devoted%20her%20life%20to%20this%20profession%2C%20and%20at%20the%20tail%20end%20of%20her%20career%2C%20she%20had%20to%20endure%20something%20so%20vicious.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdvisory%20board%20chair%20Dr.%20Manju%20Samuel%20of%20Indian%20Nurses%20Association%20of%20South%20Florida%20urged%20lawmakers%20to%20act%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20no%20specific%20laws%20to%20protect%20healthcare%20staff.%20That%20deficiency%20must%